text: Duslyk () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Gafurovsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 2,145 as of 2010. There are 39 streets. == Geography == It is located 9 km from Tuymazy. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tuymazinsky District
title: Duslyk
